 The  All Progressive Congress (APC) Progressive Young Women Forum (APC-PYWF) has congratulated  the new National Women Leader of the party, Dr Betta Edu, saying she would perform creditably. In a statement signed by the President of APC-PYWF, Seun Bosede Osamaye and the National Publicity Secretary, Theresa Tekenah, the forum expressed confidence that Edu in discharging the functions of her office, would work competently, with dedication, excellence and high purpose, to help the party advance its policy and governance priorities. The APC-PYWF urge all party members to support the new women leader, as the women wing has a lot to benefit from her varied skills. The statement reads: “The PYWF wishes  Edu a successful period in office as she takes on the onerous task of being the National Women Leader of the party. We have confidence  that  Edu in discharging the functions of her office, would work competently, with dedication, excellence and high purpose, to help the party advance its policy and governance priorities. “She has our best wishes and encouragement and may the guidance and protection of God be with her as she begins the task. “We  at APC-PYWF urge all party members to support the new Women Leader, as the women wing has a lot to benefit from her varied skills.”